uperpowers/specs/2026-07-04-lolarr-notifications-design.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "concept_notification_dedup_toast_once", "label": "\"Toast exactly once\" Dedup Strategy", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "docs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-04-lolarr-notifications-design.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Server persists/dedupes notifications with a stable id (unique on user+tmdb+media_type+kind); client seeds a Set of already-seen ids on first snapshot without toasting (backlog becomes badge-only), then toasts each new id exactly once, keeping read-state server-side/cross-device while toast display stays per-device."}, {"id": "concept_poll_not_sse", "label": "Poll (~45s) instead of SSE/WebSocket Realtime Push", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "docs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-04-lolarr-notifications-design.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Media-available events are minute-scale, so SSE/WebSocket complexity (especially on the Tizen webview) isn't justified for V1; a lightweight dedicated poll suffices and is upgradeable later."}, {"id": "concept_username_matching_no_email_fallback", "label": "Username-based User Matching (no email fallback)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "docs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-04-lolarr-notifications-design.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "requestedBy_username is matched case-insensitively against users.name because Seerr requires Jellyfin auth (guaranteed by the Silent-QC flow); there is no email field in the users table, so renamed Seerr display names are a documented risk accepted for V1."}], "edges": [{"source": "docs_superpowers_specs_2026_07_04_lolarr_notificatio